in things like taking cold showers

00:07:09.830 --> 00:07:13.810
and taking ice baths for
many different purposes.

00:07:13.810 --> 00:07:18.300
Sometimes this is introduced
as just a general health tonic,

00:07:18.300 --> 00:07:21.430
but other times people
get specific about how

00:07:21.430 --> 00:07:22.900
it can improve resilience

00:07:22.900 --> 00:07:25.703
or it can improve one's metabolism.

00:07:27.050 --> 00:07:29.950
Could you just tell me a little bit about

00:07:29.950 --> 00:07:34.950
what happens when I get into
a cold shower or an ice bath?

00:07:34.950 --> 00:07:36.970
What are some of the basic responses

00:07:36.970 --> 00:07:38.900
at the level of metabolism?

00:07:38.900 --> 00:07:41.540
Obviously psychologically,
we don't know exactly.

00:07:41.540 --> 00:07:42.870
It'll vary from person to person,

00:07:42.870 --> 00:07:46.220
but what happens when I
submerge myself into an ice bath

00:07:46.220 --> 00:07:48.273
if I've never done it before?

00:07:49.160 --> 00:07:52.230
- Well, first of all, you
get a tremendous shock.

00:07:52.230 --> 00:07:54.760
And what that's going to translate into

00:07:54.760 --> 00:07:57.330
is a bit of a shot of adrenaline.

00:07:57.330 --> 00:08:01.300
And I think this is really
the so-called benefit,

00:08:01.300 --> 00:08:04.660
but I wouldn't call it a
benefit, of the cryo chambers.

00:08:04.660 --> 00:08:06.840
You go into a cryo
chamber and it's a shock.

00:08:06.840 --> 00:08:08.840
So you get a shot of adrenaline. So, sure.

00:08:08.840 --> 00:08:11.130
You're going to feel
different when you come out.

00:08:11.130 --> 00:08:12.930
You've had a shot of adrenaline.

00:08:12.930 --> 00:08:16.880
But it doesn't necessarily
translate into any benefit

00:08:16.880 --> 00:08:21.080
in terms of your physiology
or performance, and so forth.

00:08:21.080 --> 00:08:25.440
Now if you take a cold
bath or a cold shower,

00:08:25.440 --> 00:08:27.020
a couple of things are happening.

00:08:27.020 --> 00:08:30.500
One is you're going to
stimulate vasoconstriction.

00:08:30.500 --> 00:08:31.470
So if anything,

00:08:31.470 --> 00:08:33.250
it's going to make it a
little bit more difficult

00:08:33.250 --> 00:08:35.260
for your body to get rid of heat,

00:08:35.260 --> 00:08:40.260
because you're shutting off
your avenues of heat loss.

00:08:40.280 --> 00:08:43.560
If you're in a true cold bath,

00:08:43.560 --> 00:08:47.470
the overall surface area
of your body is so great

00:08:47.470 --> 00:08:49.840
that it doesn't matter if
you're vasoconstricted,

00:08:49.840 --> 00:08:51.350
you're still going to lose heat.

00:08:51.350 --> 00:08:55.150
- Okay, so vasoconstriction,
the constriction of,

00:08:55.150 --> 00:08:58.820
is it capillaries, vessels
and arteries all constrict

00:08:58.820 --> 00:09:01.710
or just one or two?

00:09:01.710 --> 00:09:05.370
- Well, this is an area of controversy.

00:09:05.370 --> 00:09:07.900
In general, when people
talk of vasoconstriction,

00:09:07.900 --> 00:09:11.793
they talk of the overall skin
surface, and that is not true.

00:09:13.000 --> 00:09:15.190
The primary sites of heat loss,

00:09:15.190 --> 00:09:17.140
which we're going to get into,

00:09:17.140 --> 00:09:18.890
are the palms of your hands,

00:09:18.890 --> 00:09:22.650
the soles of your feet, and
the upper part of your face.

00:09:22.650 --> 00:09:25.780
And the reason these are
avenues for heat loss

00:09:25.780 --> 00:09:28.900
is they're underlain by
special blood vessels.

00:09:28.900 --> 00:09:32.810
And these blood vessels
are able to shunt the blood

00:09:32.810 --> 00:09:35.810
from the arteries, which
are coming from the heart,

00:09:35.810 --> 00:09:37.500
directly to the veins,

00:09:37.500 --> 00:09:38.990
which are returning to the heart,

00:09:38.990 --> 00:09:40.930
and bypassing the capillaries,

00:09:40.930 --> 00:09:44.600
which are the nutritive
vessels, but high resistance.

00:09:44.600 --> 00:09:47.270
So you can tell when
you shake someone's hand

00:09:47.270 --> 00:09:49.750
what his or her thermal status is.

00:09:49.750 --> 00:09:51.450
The hand's hot or it's cold.

00:09:51.450 --> 00:09:52.810
- Do you think that's part of the reason

00:09:52.810 --> 00:09:55.995
why humans evolved this
practice of shaking hands?

00:09:55.995 --> 00:09:56.828
[Craig chuckles]

00:09:56.828 --> 00:09:58.540
Assessing each other's level of anxiety?

00:09:58.540 --> 00:10:01.780
We all know that a limp
shake is pretty indicative

00:10:01.780 --> 00:10:03.310
of something and a firm handshake

00:10:03.310 --> 00:10:04.560
is indicatives of something,

00:10:04.560 --> 00:10:07.420
as is the crushing handshake
for that matter, right?

00:10:07.420 --> 00:10:09.960
- Yeah, I really don't know
what the evolutionary origin

00:10:09.960 --> 00:10:12.700
of handshaking is, other
than to get your hand away

00:10:12.700 --> 00:10:14.800
from your weapon, [chuckles] perhaps.

00:10:14.800 --> 00:10:16.760
- Right, a couple of questions

00:10:16.760 --> 00:10:21.370
before we get into these
specialized vascular compartments

00:10:21.370 --> 00:10:24.890
on the soles, the palms
and the upper face.

00:10:24.890 --> 00:10:26.840
You mentioned whole body immersion,

00:10:26.840 --> 00:10:30.420
like into an ice bath or very
cold water up to the neck

00:10:30.420 --> 00:10:31.920
versus a cold shower.

00:10:31.920 --> 00:10:34.590
Is there something fundamentally
different about those two,

00:10:34.590 --> 00:10:36.330
besides the fact that they both provide

00:10:36.330 --> 00:10:37.810
their release of adrenaline?

00:10:37.810 --> 00:10:40.310
Is there anything that's really important

00:10:40.310 --> 00:10:42.360
to understand about the difference

00:10:42.360 --> 00:10:44.490
in the physiological response evoked

00:10:44.490 --> 00:10:48.540
by cold shower versus immersion in cold?

00:10:48.540 --> 00:10:51.420
- Well, there are differences
that are more physical

00:10:51.420 --> 00:10:52.420
than anything else.

00:10:52.420 --> 00:10:55.460
So if you are in a cold
bath and you're still,

00:10:55.460 --> 00:10:57.790
you develop a boundary layer.

00:10:57.790 --> 00:10:58.760
If you're in a shower,

00:10:58.760 --> 00:10:59.750
you can't develop a boundary layer.

