00:17:05.210 --> 00:17:07.230
So like a steam engine,

00:17:07.230 --> 00:17:12.020
most of the energy in
our food is lost as heat.

00:17:12.020 --> 00:17:15.150
So we are roughly about 20% efficient.

00:17:15.150 --> 00:17:17.860
So of the energy that
we take in in our food,

00:17:17.860 --> 00:17:20.470
about 20% of that can go into doing work,

00:17:20.470 --> 00:17:22.920
and the rest of it is lost as heat.

00:17:22.920 --> 00:17:24.560
Now we're mammals.

00:17:24.560 --> 00:17:27.750
We use that heat to keep our
body temperature considerably

00:17:27.750 --> 00:17:29.530
above the environment.

00:17:29.530 --> 00:17:34.190
But if you raise body
temperature a few degrees higher,

00:17:34.190 --> 00:17:37.860
you're in trouble, that's hyperthermia.

00:17:37.860 --> 00:17:41.780
So individual muscles can
reach hyperthermic limits

00:17:41.780 --> 00:17:45.550
