it in the whole body.

00:17:45.550 --> 00:17:50.550
So to keep you from damaging
your muscle by hyperthermia,

00:17:50.690 --> 00:17:52.610
we have fail-safe mechanisms.

00:17:52.610 --> 00:17:56.390
And one of those fail-safe
mechanisms is an enzyme

00:17:56.390 --> 00:17:59.600
which is critical for getting fuel.

00:17:59.600 --> 00:18:04.440
In other words, the results
of metabolism of glucose,

00:18:04.440 --> 00:18:06.870
getting that fuel into the mitochondria,

00:18:06.870 --> 00:18:09.640
which is making our major coinage

00:18:09.640 --> 00:18:12.790
of energy exchange, ATP, okay?

00:18:12.790 --> 00:18:16.870
So that particular enzyme
is temperature-sensitive.

00:18:16.870 --> 00:18:20.700
So when the muscle temperature
gets above 39 or 39.5,

00:18:20.700 --> 00:18:22.170
it shuts off.

00:18:22.170 --> 00:18:25.340
And that essentially
shuts off the fuel supply

00:18:25.340 --> 00:18:26.440
to the mitochondria.

00:18:26.440 --> 00:18:28.960
That's when you cannot do one more rep.

